intro: Andryala pinnatifida f. webbii, commonly known as the webbii form of the narrow-leaved andryala, is a flowering plant native to certain regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the familyApiaceae, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided, pinnatifid leaves. The plant typically grows in moist, shaded environments such as forest understories. Its flowers are small and clustered in umbels, a common feature among members of its family. It is valued in traditional medicine for its purported health benefits.
